# Repeating Card Meanings — Editorial Reinsertion Contract

Mandatory for all 78 cards. See `editorial/repeating-card-library/03_EDITORIAL_REINSERTION_CONTRACT.md`.

## Only editable areas

1. **Body copy** beneath existing headings (paragraphs, blockquote text, list item text)
2. **Frontmatter values** only for fields explicitly listed in `contracts/{suit}/{slug}.yaml` under `allowed_frontmatter_edits`

## Everything else is immutable

Slugs, URLs, headings, section names/order, anchors, IDs, frontmatter keys/order, unapproved frontmatter values, schema, JSON-LD, breadcrumbs, components, rendering, CSS, data model, internal links, navigation, images, structural markdown.

## Dual URL surfaces (intentional, not a defect)

One markdown source powers two public routes:

- Entity: `/repeating-card-meanings/{card-slug}/`
- Tool: `/tools/repeating-card-meanings/{collection-id}/`

Both read the same `repeatingCardMeanings` collection entry. This is by design.

## Diagnostic discipline

- **Read-only by default** for investigations: no experimental edits to production card files, no cache clears, no builds unless explicitly authorised for reinsertion QA.
- **Never modify card files to reproduce warnings** (e.g. append newlines, touch mtimes).
- Astro `[glob-loader] Duplicate id` on content digest change is a **misleading sync warning**, not a real ID collision. Do not treat it as a blocking defect unless `npm run audit:rcm-integrity` reports duplicate collection IDs, slugs, or canonicals.

## Blocking integrity failures

`npm run audit:rcm-integrity` must pass before and after every reinsertion. These are **blocking**:

- Wrong card count or suit counts (must be 78: majors 22, each minor suit 14)
- Duplicate Astro collection IDs (`majors/the-fool`, etc.)
- Duplicate frontmatter `slug` values
- Duplicate `canonicalUrl` values
- More than one source file per card

## Before every reinsertion

```bash
npm run audit:rcm-integrity
node scripts/validate-rcm-editorial-reinsertion.mjs \
  --contract editorial/repeating-card-library/contracts/{suit}/{slug}.yaml \
  editorial/repeating-card-library/claude/{suit}/{slug}.md
```

Or use the orchestrated workflow (pre/post audit, archive, production write, `.astro` cache clear, sync, build):

```bash
node scripts/reinsert-rcm-editorial.mjs \
  --contract editorial/repeating-card-library/contracts/{suit}/{slug}.yaml
```

Dry run (audit + contract only):

```bash
node scripts/reinsert-rcm-editorial.mjs --contract ... --dry-run
```

If validation or integrity audit fails: **stop and report differences**. Do not write to production. Do not auto-fix.

## Production path (only)

`src/content/repeating-card-meanings/{suit}/{slug}.md`
